<div class="headLeft headFull">
<h1>The Best Manhattan Hotels</h1>
</div>
</div>
<div class="colLeft">
<div class="addthis_inline_share_toolbox" style="    text-align: right;"></div>
<p>An exhilarating, energetic, eclectic melting pot, New York is a truly cosmopolitan city, where every language is spoken, every race represented and every cuisine is on the menu. And the best Manhattan hotels reflect that variety.</p>
<p><span class="image-box"><img src="https://www.thehotelguru.com/_images/4a/4d/4a4df75bcaaea9c7de492d41ac998e91/500x332.jpg" alt="Manhattan" /></span><span class="caption-overlay" style="float: right;
    position: relative;
    clear: both;
    display: inline;
    margin: -26px 107px 0 0;
    background-color: white;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
    font-size: 10px;"><a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/thomashawk/" target="_blank">Flickr user Thomas Hawk</a></span></p>
<p>As you'd expect in such a vibrant place, the best Manhattan hotels come with a vastly varied price list. But there&rsquo;s really nowhere like Downtown Manhattan to experience, and the only way to experience New York is in one of our Guru&rsquo;s recommendations for the best Manhattan hotels.</p>
<h1>The Best Manhattan Hotels</h1>
<h2>For the classic New York experience</h2>
<p><span class="image-box"><img src="https://www.thehotelguru.com/_images/74/cb/74cb9d7e4dab85503870afe623835091/500x332.jpg" alt="Gramercy Park Hotel" /></span></p>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="/hotel/gramercy-park-hotel-new-york">Gramercy Park Hotel</a> is a luxurious boutique hotel right by Gramercy Park, with an award winning roof terrace restaurant overlooking the park and an impressive art collection which includes Warhol and Damien Hirst.</li>
<li><a href="/hotel/the-mercer-new-york">The Mercer</a> is another New York classic, offering the ultimate in SoHo design chic and a world-class restaurant.</li>
</ul>
<h2>For a city break</h2>
<p><span class="image-box"><img src="https://www.thehotelguru.com/_images/c8/73/c87384e096a280acb021fc8b55de9081/500x332.jpg" alt="Soho Grand Hotel" /></span></p>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="/hotel/washington-square-hotel-new-york">Washington Square Hotel</a> is a historic hotel in Greenwich village, with Art Deco details, subtly lit rooms and a great restaurant.</li>
<li>But the <a href="/hotel/soho-grand-hotel-new-york">SoHo Grand Hotel</a> is a more sumptuous option with stunning views, renowned decor and acclaimed cuisine.</li>
</ul>
<h2>For hip style</h2>
<p><span class="image-box"><img src="https://www.thehotelguru.com/_images/b5/8c/b58cb4b0d57119e75b23bc677263b8f1/500x332.jpg" alt="Sixty Soho" /></span></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/hotel/sixty-soho-new-york">Sixty Soho</a> is a hip SoHo hotel with a phenomenal rooftop bar and restaurant,</li>
<li>or try <a href="/hotel/soho-house-new-york">Soho House</a>, for exclusive luxury in the Meatpacking district with an even more fantastic rooftop terrace and pool, a deluxe spa and a 44-seat cinema.</li>
</ul>
<h2>For the city buzz</h2>
<p><span class="image-box"><img src="https://www.thehotelguru.com/_images/36/8a/368aa2321b542f7e4e2ae4489a91c061/500x332.jpg" alt="The Bowery" /></span></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/hotel/the-bowery-hotel-new-york">The Bowery Hotel</a> is a fun and lively destination in an up-an-coming district,</li>
<li>or you could go for the <a href="/hotel/the-standard-new-york">The Standard</a> in the uber cool Meatpacking District, with it&rsquo;s ceiling to floor windows offering views across the whole buzzing scene.</li>
<li>The <a href="/hotel/tribeca-grand-new-york">Tribeca Grand</a> is another of our buzziest and best Manhattan hotels with an in-house cinema, funky roof-top terrace, regular live music and plenty of luxury.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Best Manhattan hotels on Wall Street</h2>
<p><span class="image-box"><img src="https://www.thehotelguru.com/_images/db/71/db71fab423cf56de447eeea623e0a821/500x332.jpg" alt="Andaz Wall Street" /></span></p>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="/hotel/andaz-wall-street-new-york">Andaz Wall Street</a> is worth a mention as the only hotel with a Wall Street address. It&rsquo;s hip and happening and has a fantastic spa and bar.</li>
</ul>
<h3>If you haven&rsquo;t found the best Manhattan hotel for you on our Guru&rsquo;s list then try:</h3>
<ul>
<li>expanding your search to include our list of the <a href="/search?searchbox=topbar&amp;loc=&amp;locname=manhattan">best places to stay in New York</a>,</li>
<li>refining your list to the <a href="/best-hotels/united-states-of-america/new-york-midtown-and-uptown">best Midtown and Uptown Manhattan Hotels</a>,</li>
<li>or <a href="/advice-and-booking/enquire">contact</a> one of our friendly Gurus for advice.</li>
</ul>
<h1>The Best Manhattan Hotels</h1>
<p><div id="hotelResults" class="hotelResults"><ul class="hotels" id="hotels">
<li class="hotel" id="hotel-476" data-hotel-id="476">
<div class="imgWrap">
<a href="/hotel/gramercy-park-hotel-new-york" class="hotel-link">
<img src="https://www.thehotelguru.com/_images/74/cb/74cb9d7e4dab85503870afe623835091/s440x294.jpg" alt="Gramercy Park Hotel">
<br /><a href="/hotel/gramercy-park-hotel-new-york" class="hotel-link">See more photos</a>
</a>
</div>
<div class="infoWrap">
<h3>
<a href="/hotel/gramercy-park-hotel-new-york" class="hotel-link">Gramercy Park Hotel</a>
<span class="roomsInfo">
185 rooms
from <b>£268</b>
</span>
</h3>
<span class="location">New York</span>
<div class="desc">
<p>Newly decorated luxury boutique. Great pieces of furniture and diverse artworks, from Warhol to Damien Hirst, provide a unique impression of 21st century Bohemia. A lively and hip destination.</p>
<div><b>Luxury</b></div><div><b>Sights nearby</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;-&nbsp;&nbsp;Just a short stroll away you will find New Yorks most famous site, The Empire State Building.</div><div><b>Great walks</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;-&nbsp;&nbsp;Take a turn around the lovely Gramercy Park literally on the hotels doorstep.</div><div><b>Views</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;-&nbsp;&nbsp;Gorgeous views of Gramercy Park</div><div><b>Recommended by</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;-&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr &amp; Mrs Smith, Tablet, Frommers, Kiwi Collection</div>
</div>
